        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 7:29PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 729 PM MDT, trained weather spotters reported a strong
thunderstorm over northeastern Colorado Springs, moving southeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northeastern Colorado Springs, Schriever Space Force Base, Ellicott,
Falcon, and Cimarron Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
